body:
Hello i'm facing a problem after updating `android studio to arctic fox`, Autocomplete is take about 10 second to display!!
Although it working fine with native java and kotlin and i don't have any issues with `flutter doctor`.

I have tried to delete cache and tried also deleting `flutter sdk` and `flutter && dart plugins` then re-install doesn't solve my problem.
I have also disabled `Add unambiguous imports on the fly` and `Optimize imports on the fly` from auto import
My Laptop is lenovo ideapad z500 / core i5 / 12 gb ram / 120 hyperx kingston ssd with ubuntu 20.04 stable.
Dart plugin is: `203.8292` and flutter plugin is: `59.0.2`.

comment_data.body:
Please paste the output of running `flutter doctor -v` from the command line. Also attach your `idea.log` file; you can find it from `Help > Show log in files` (or something similar).

The options you disabled only apply to Java. There is a Dart option on that page, but I don't think it will change anything for you.

Can you give us an estimate of how large or complex your project is?

Here is `flutter doctor -v`  result:

And `idea.log` Result [here](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1UCAVzgtFFNf6WGrUMTe-TamebPPGZCPT/view?usp=sharing). 
This problem happen with new project no thing added.
Thanks. Can you do an experiment? Disable all optional plugins except Dart and Flutter, and restart. Does the problem still occur?

Sorry to hear autocomplete is running so much slower. If you open a different Flutter application are you still able to repro the slowness?
`git clone https://github.com/flutter/gallery.git`
would be a good sample medium sized application to test.

Thanks For replay i have already tested that and again i re-test but unfortunately the same issue i also downloaded premium `IntelliJ idea ultimate edition` i'm facing the same issue, i don't know why after upgrading i'm facing this issue.
I also tried on `vscode` it works fine without any problems and i said before native java and kotlin and also `Jetpack compose` works fine without any problems.
Can you do an experiment? Disable all optional plugins except Dart and Flutter, and restart. Does the problem still occur?

Sir as i told you on the previous comment i have already done that and i have also installed `IntelliJ` without any plugin no thing changed, I have notice something when i write `CPU` record about 90% and `Memory` record about 60% although i'm running only `android studio` and No Emulator or Web Browser.
It may be caused by the Flutter 2.5.0 version. I also have this problem, so I have to use Vscode, hoping to solve this problem soon. thanks

> It may be caused by the Flutter 2.5.0 version. I also have this problem, so I have to use Vscode, hoping to solve this problem soon. thanks

after i upgrande to 2.5.2 autocomplete become normally..

> > 可能是 Flutter 2.5.0 版本导致的。我也有这个问题，所以只好用Vscode，希望早日解决这个问题。谢谢
> 
> 在我升级到 2.5.2 自动完成后变得正常..

thanks, I am also normal
Thanks a lot fixed on version `2.6.0`

milestone.description: Work triaged but not yet planned for a specific release.
